The paper deals with the problem of generating recommendations, which is a common topic in machine learning and information retrieval. The use of co-clustering is a technique that is often used in recommendation systems, and falls under the category of unsupervised learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely categories. The paper also mentions the scalability of the approach, which suggests that it may fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the technique on GPUs, which falls under cs.SI (Systems and Control).
